body.text:
This is a matter of reputation and accountability. 

The university's message is a bold declaration, but a declaration is only as strong as the actions that follow it. 

To truly rebuild public trust, they must do more than just condemn corruption; they must prove their commitment to transparency.

​The talk of "due process" is wise, as it prevents reckless accusations. 

But the real measure of their resolve will be in how they handle those accusations—with an open hand, and an honest heart. Only then will their words carry weight.

They are guided by their mission and values, and that they will uphold accountability and transparency.

This is an admirable stance.

However, the true test will be in the implementation. 

A mere statement, no matter how eloquent, is just a promise. 

A true leader fulfills promises.
